        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36119",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=polothy",
                        "name": "polothy",
                        "displayName": "Mark Nielsen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I seem to be having the same problem, the processes run forever.  I tried the ZendX_Console_Process_UnixTest::testParallel() code and it failed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=polothy",
                        "name": "polothy",
                        "displayName": "Mark Nielsen",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-18T13:18:20.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-18T13:18:20.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37279",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=flo",
                        "name": "flo",
                        "displayName": "Florian Hoenig",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "Same problem here!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=flo",
                        "name": "flo",
                        "displayName": "Florian Hoenig",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-31T14:18:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-31T14:18:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37373",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=flo",
                        "name": "flo",
                        "displayName": "Florian Hoenig",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "\r\nThis will fix the problem on OSX's WAITPID behavior (Linux not yet tested):\r\n\r\npublic function isRunning()\r\n{   \r\n    $this->_isRunning = (0 == pcntl_waitpid($this->_pid, $status, WNOHANG));\r\n    return $this->_isRunning;\r\n}\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=flo",
                        "name": "flo",
                        "displayName": "Florian Hoenig",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-04T14:26:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-04T14:26:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37426",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=scramatte",
                        "name": "scramatte",
                        "displayName": "S\u00e9bastien Cramatte",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The isRunning() fix seems to works under Linux too. \r\nI've tested under Debian Lenny.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=scramatte",
                        "name": "scramatte",
                        "displayName": "S\u00e9bastien Cramatte",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-06T02:13:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-06T02:13:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37497",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=flo",
                        "name": "flo",
                        "displayName": "Florian Hoenig",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "Here is another fix.\r\n\r\nshmop_read returns a string and therefore it's ($okay === \"0\") instead of === 0.\r\n\r\n\r\n    \/**\r\n     * Wait for IPC Semaphore\r\n     * \r\n     * @return void\r\n     *\/\r\n    private function _waitForIpcSemaphore()\r\n    {\r\n        while (true) {\r\n            $okay = shmop_read($this->_internalSemKey, 0, 1);\r\n            if ($okay === \"0\") {\r\n                break;\r\n            }\r\n            usleep(10);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\n\r\nLooks like the class is based on PHP_Fork from PEAR. Really needs some redesign.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=flo",
                        "name": "flo",
                        "displayName": "Florian Hoenig",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-07T13:27:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-07T13:27:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39629",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tyrael",
                        "name": "tyrael",
                        "displayName": "Ferenc Kovacs",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've had the the same problem, it seems that the isRunning is only good for checking, whether the process started or not.\r\nSo I implemented an isFinished method with a getFinished and _setFinished.\r\nisFinished() returns whether or not the process is finished running, getFinished returns when was the _setFinished called, so it can be used for measuring the execution time.\r\n\r\nI'm gonna attach the patch.\r\n\r\nTyrael",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tyrael",
                        "name": "tyrael",
                        "displayName": "Ferenc Kovacs",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-29T05:45:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-29T05:45:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39630",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tyrael",
                        "name": "tyrael",
                        "displayName": "Ferenc Kovacs",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "isFinished, getFinished, _setFinished",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tyrael",
                        "name": "tyrael",
                        "displayName": "Ferenc Kovacs",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-03-29T05:46:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-03-29T05:46:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39637",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tyrael",
                        "name": "tyrael",
                        "displayName": "Ferenc Kovacs",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "sorry, I missed something from the patch.\r\nI wanted to set the actual time in the _setFinished method, so the \"true\" should be \"time()\" there.\r\n\r\nTyrael",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tyrael",
                        "name": "tyrael",
